name: evolution_strategy
version: "1.0.0"
language: zig
module: tri.evolution_strategy

description: |
  Evolution Strategy — ASHA+PBT inspired agent strategy optimization.

  Unlike competitors (Kiro static steering, Claude Code context-only):
    - Strategies EVOLVE based on episode success/failure data
    - ASHA: prune strategies that fail 3+ times (MNL pattern)
    - PBT: copy parameters from successful strategies to struggling ones

  Commands:
    tri evolve status    — show current strategy fitness
    tri evolve mutate    — generate strategy variations
    tri evolve select    — prune worst, promote best
    tri evolve history   — show evolution generations

  Storage:
    .trinity/evolution/strategies/{gen}_{name}.json
    .trinity/evolution/fitness_log.json
    .trinity/evolution/generations.json

behaviors:
  - name: evaluateFitness
    given: Strategy with episode results
    when: Called on tri evolve status
    then: |
      Fitness = success_rate * 0.4 + speed * 0.3 + quality * 0.3
      Where quality = compile_rate from generated specs.
      Return ranked strategies.

  - name: mutateStrategy
    given: Top-performing strategy
    when: Called on tri evolve mutate
    then: |
      Create 3 variations:
        1. Safe: +-5% on one parameter
        2. Balanced: +-15% on two parameters
        3. Bold: reshuffle approach entirely
      Save to next generation directory.

  - name: selectStrategies
    given: All strategies in current generation
    when: Called on tri evolve select
    then: |
      ASHA prune: kill bottom 33% by fitness.
      PBT exploit: copy top parameters to mid-tier.
      PBT explore: random perturbation on copies.
      Advance generation counter.

  - name: showHistory
    given: All generation logs
    when: Called on tri evolve history
    then: |
      Show fitness curves across generations.
      Highlight best-ever strategy.
      Show mutation lineage.

export_functions:
  - evaluateFitness
  - mutateStrategy
  - selectStrategies
  - showHistory
